<h1>Routing &amp; pages</h1>

<p>
    Files in <code>Pages/</code> become URLs at build time. The Nxt source generator walks
    the directory, derives a route pattern from the file path, and emits a
    <code>[Route]</code> attribute on the page's compiled partial class so Blazor's router
    picks it up.
</p>

<h2>The basics</h2>
<table>
    <thead><tr><th>File</th><th>URL</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>Pages/Index.razor</code></td><td><code>/</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>Pages/About.razor</code></td><td><code>/about</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>Pages/Blog/Index.razor</code></td><td><code>/blog</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>Pages/Blog/Post.razor</code></td><td><code>/blog/post</code></td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<p>URLs are lowercased automatically; folders become path segments.</p>

<h2>Dynamic segments</h2>
<p>Wrap a filename segment in square brackets to capture it as a route parameter.</p>
<table>
    <thead><tr><th>File</th><th>URL pattern</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>Pages/Blog/[slug].razor</code></td><td><code>/blog/&#123;slug&#125;</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>Pages/Users/[id]/Posts.razor</code></td><td><code>/users/&#123;id&#125;/posts</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>Pages/Files/[...path].razor</code></td><td><code>/files/&#123;*path&#125;</code> (catch-all)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<p>Bind the captured value via a parameter property:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;h1&gt;Post: @@Slug&lt;/h1&gt;

@@code &#123;
    [Parameter] public string Slug &#123; get; set; &#125; = "";
&#125;</code></pre>

<h2>Render modes (via magic comment)</h2>
<p>Stick a magic comment at the top of the file to change how it renders:</p>
<pre><code>@@* @@nxt:static *@@                  → SSG (build-time prerender)
@@* @@nxt:revalidate=60 *@@           → ISR (cached, regenerate every 60s)
@@* @@nxt:interactive-server *@@      → SSR + Blazor Server hydration
@@* @@nxt:interactive-wasm *@@        → SSR + Blazor WebAssembly hydration
@@* @@nxt:layout=My.Custom.Layout *@@ → override the auto-detected layout</code></pre>

<p>Without any directive, the page is plain SSR.</p>

<h2>Razor (<code>.cshtml</code>) pages</h2>
<p>
    Drop a <code>.cshtml</code> file in <code>Pages/</code> and it's routed the same way as
    a Razor component. The runtime renders it via the MVC Razor view engine. Use this when
    you need the Razor Pages programming model (e.g., <code>ViewData</code>,
    <code>@@inject</code> in views) instead of Blazor.
</p>
